  "title": "Musculocutaneous nerve",
  "body_html": "<b>Musculocutaneous Nerve Key Points</b><br /><ul><li>Arises from the lateral cord of the brachial plexus. </li><li>Derived from C5, C6 and C7 nerve roots</li><li>Supplies anterior compartment of arm (brachialis, biceps brachii and coracobrachialis)</li><li>Injuries to nerve result in motor weakness of elbow flexion and supination of the forearm. Sensory loss to lateral cutaneous area of forearm</li></ul><br /><br /><div class=\"text-center\"><table><tr><td align = 'left' colspan='2'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/fti846b.png'><img class='ajaximage' src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/fti846.png'/></a></td></tr><tr><td valign='top' align='left'></td><td align='right'></td></tr></table></div><div class='imagetext'>Anatomical location of musculocutaneous nerve. <b>Click on image to enlarge</b></div><br /><div class=\"text-center\"><table><tr><td align = 'left' colspan='2'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/fti847b.png'><img class='ajaximage' src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/fti847.png'/></a></td></tr><tr><td valign='top' align='left'></td><td align='right'></td></tr></table></div><div class='imagetext'>Illustration showing course of the musculocutaneous nerve. <b>Click on image to enlarge</b></div></div>\n\n<div id=\"mybodylinks\"></div>\n\n<div id=\"mybodymedia\"><table><tr><td colspan=\"2\"><a href=\"#\" class=\"media_link\" data-url=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/Wru7UCHlbFU\" data-description=\"Musculocutabeous nerve anatomy\" data-media=\"97\"><img border=\"0\" alt=\"YouTube\" src=\"https://i1.ytimg.com/vi/Wru7UCHlbFU/mqdefault.jpg\" style=\"max-width:150px;\"></a></td></tr><tr ><td style=\"padding-top:10px\" colspan=\"2\"><a style=\"\" href=\"#\" class=\"media_link\" data-url=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/Wru7UCHlbFU\" data-media=\"97\">Musculocutabeous nerve anatomy</a></td></tr><tr><td><span ><small>Anatomy zone - YouTube</small></span></td><td style = \"float: right;width:115px;\"><button type=\"button\" style=\"\" id=\"media_like_123\" data-mediaid=\"123\" data-rating=\"1\" class=\"rate-media btn btn-link\"><svg class=\"bi bi-hand-thumbs-up\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\"><use xlink:href=\"#icon-hand-thumbs-up\"/></svg></button><span id=\"media_good_count_123\" class = \"media_good_count\" style=\"color:green; font-size:85%;\">0</span><button type=\"button\" style=\"\" id=\"media_dislike_123\" data-mediaid=\"123\" data-rating=\"0\" class=\"rate-media btn btn-link\"><svg class=\"bi bi-hand-thumbs-down\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\"><use xlink:href=\"#icon-hand-thumbs-down\"/></svg></button><span id=\"media_bad_count_123\" class = \"media_bad_count\" style=\"color:red; font-size:85%;\">0</span></td></tr></table></div>\n\n\n<div id=\"categorynum\">1</div>\n\n<div id=\"subcategorynum\">6</div>\n\n<div id=\"categoryname\">Anatomy</div>\n\n<div id=\"subcategoryname\">Upper limb</div>\n<div id=\"mybody\">\n\n<div id=\"body_content\">\n<b>Musculocutaneous Nerve Key Points</b><br /><ul><li>Arises from the lateral cord of the brachial plexus. </li><li>Derived from C5, C6 and C7 nerve roots</li><li>Supplies anterior compartment of arm (brachialis, biceps brachii and coracobrachialis)</li><li>Injuries to nerve result in motor weakness of elbow flexion and supination of the forearm. Sensory loss to lateral cutaneous area of forearm</li></ul><br /><br /><div class=\"text-center\"><table><tr><td align = 'left' colspan='2'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/fti846b.png'><img class='ajaximage' src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/fti846.png'/></a></td></tr><tr><td valign='top' align='left'></td><td align='right'></td></tr></table></div><div class='imagetext'>Anatomical location of musculocutaneous nerve. <b>Click on image to enlarge</b></div><br /><div class=\"text-center\"><table><tr><td align = 'left' colspan='2'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/fti847b.png'><img class='ajaximage' src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/fti847.png'/></a></td></tr><tr><td valign='top' align='left'></td><td align='right'></td></tr></table></div><div class='imagetext'>Illustration showing course of the musculocutaneous nerve. <b>Click on image to enlarge</b></div></div>\n\n\n<BR><BR><br><br><table><tr><td colspan=\"2\"><a href=\"#\" class=\"media_link\" data-url=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/Wru7UCHlbFU\" data-description=\"Musculocutabeous nerve anatomy\" data-media=\"97\"><img border=\"0\" alt=\"YouTube\" src=\"https://i1.ytimg.com/vi/Wru7UCHlbFU/mqdefault.jpg\" style=\"max-width:150px;\"></a></td></tr><tr ><td style=\"padding-top:10px\" colspan=\"2\"><a style=\"\" href=\"#\" class=\"media_link\" data-url=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/Wru7UCHlbFU\" data-media=\"97\">Musculocutabeous nerve anatomy</a></td></tr><tr><td><span ><small>Anatomy zone - YouTube</small></span></td><td style = \"float: right;width:115px;\"><button type=\"button\" style=\"\" id=\"media_like_123\" data-mediaid=\"123\" data-rating=\"1\" class=\"rate-media btn btn-link\"><svg class=\"bi bi-hand-thumbs-up\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\"><use xlink:href=\"#icon-hand-thumbs-up\"/></svg></button><span id=\"media_good_count_123\" class = \"media_good_count\" style=\"color:green; font-size:85%;\">0</span><button type=\"button\" style=\"\" id=\"media_dislike_123\" data-mediaid=\"123\" data-rating=\"0\" class=\"rate-media btn btn-link\"><svg class=\"bi bi-hand-thumbs-down\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\"><use xlink:href=\"#icon-hand-thumbs-down\"/></svg></button><span id=\"media_bad_count_123\" class = \"media_bad_count\" style=\"color:red; font-size:85%;\">0</span></td></tr></table>",
